To check the version of tomcat currently running in your machine.

go to the home folder of tomcat. i.e where tomcat is installed.
Inside the bin folder of tomcat there is a filde called 
version.sh
version.batr

run the file

sh version.sh

Ouput is as follows (will vary depending on each setup)

Using CATALINA_BASE:   /opt/bitnami/apache-tomcat
Using CATALINA_HOME:   /opt/bitnami/apache-tomcat
Using CATALINA_TMPDIR: /opt/bitnami/apache-tomcat/temp
Using JRE_HOME:        /opt/bitnami/java
Using CLASSPATH:       /opt/bitnami/apache-tomcat/bin/bootstrap.jar
Server version: Apache Tomcat/6.0.33
Server built:   Aug 16 2011 02:16:34
Server number:  6.0.33.0
OS Name:        Linux
OS Version:     2.6.32-314-ec2
Architecture:   i386
JVM Version:    1.6.0_22-b04
JVM Vendor:     Sun Microsystems Inc.


